      • attachChild

        @MainThread
protected void attachChild(Router<?,?> childRouter)
        Attaches a child router to this router. This method will automatically tag the child router by its class name to namespace its saved instance state Bundle object.

        If you have multiple children of the same class, use attachChild(Router, String) to specify a custom tag.

        Parameters:
        childRouter - the Router to be attached.

      • attachChild

protected void attachChild(Router<?,?> childRouter,
                                       java.lang.String tag)
        Attaches a child router to this router.
        Parameters:
        childRouter - the Router to be attached.
        tag - an identifier to namespace saved instance state Bundle objects.

      • detachChild

        @MainThread
protected void detachChild(Router childRouter)
        Detaches the from the current Interactor. NOTE: No consumers of this API should ever keep a reference to the detached child router, leak canary will enforce that it gets garbage collected.

        If you need to keep references to previous routers, use RouterNavigator.

        Parameters:
        childRouter - the Router to be detached.
